# TEAM requirements audit — pass 1 (docs only)

When the user asks to continue TEAM pass 1, audit a TM slice, or references `requirements-audit-queue.md` in pace-team2, follow this protocol.

## Scope

- **In scope:** Update requirement slices under `docs/requirements/TM*.md` and status rows in `docs/delivery/requirements-audit-queue.md`.
- **Out of scope:** Any edit under `src/`, tests, migrations, CSS, or pass-2 implementation. Do not update [team-build-queue.md](../docs/delivery/team-build-queue.md) build status.

## Authority

| Source | Role |
|--------|------|
| `pace-prototype/apps/pace-team/` | **Layout authority** — org landing, overview, members, approvals, events, comms, forms, reports, settings |
| `pace-team2/src/` | **Read-only** — note drift; requirements target prototype layout |
| `pace-core2/packages/core/docs/standards/` | **Component and markup rules** |

Prototype is **layout only**. Do not copy hash router, mock data, Tweaks panel, or `team-styles.css` one-offs as production mandates.

## Procedure (each slice)

1. Read [requirements-audit-queue.md](../docs/delivery/requirements-audit-queue.md); select the lowest `audit_order` with `audit_status = Pending` (or resume `In progress`).
2. Set row to `In progress`.
3. Read the requirement doc, `prototype_refs`, and skim implementation hints (read-only).
4. Audit layout gaps: two-pane queues, DataTable toolbars, settings standalone pages, form authoring drawer, comms compose flow, org overview launcher grid.
5. Update **only** the requirement slice:
   - **Visual specification** (or equivalent)
   - Layout-driven acceptance criteria
   - **Prototype reference:** line with correct paths (`pages.jsx`, `pages-2.jsx`, etc.)
   - **Implementation delta (pass 2)** when prod differs or prototype missing (e.g. TM12 photo moderation)
6. Set `Done`, or `N/A` when no prototype exists (document gap explicitly for TM12).
7. Continue to next Pending slice unless the user capped the run.

## Dry run

Report gaps in chat only; do not modify files.

## Chaining

After marking Done, proceed to the next Pending slice without asking the user to repeat the audit prompt.
